2. It boosts singing songs (ones that require no instrument) by 80%. This is how bards can help provide those really insane damage shields. It is also how they can provide straight attack rating boosts. Without it, these aspects are mediocre at best.<br>
3. It procs a groupwide attack boost as well as haste that lasts for a good chunk of time.<br>
<br>
If you doubt my opinion, go ask Thott(guildleader of Afterlife). Go ask one of the bards from FoH. Go ask bards in any of the big guilds that do endgame mobs. They will all tell you that it could be a weapon on par with a rusty dagger and they would still wield it due to the effects above. Can you play a high-level bard without your epic? Yes. Are you truly effective at high-level without it? No. Our epic, unlike many of the others, is not just a status symbol. It completes our class at the high end. Without it you are relegated to providing manasong and mediocre buffs until level 60, when you get a disc that provide similiar capability for 2 min and then a nice long recycle time.<br>
<br>
I am not coming down on you per se, you are entitled to your opinion. But until you have experience playing a high level bard you can't claim to have knowledge that the bard epic is not necessary to be all you can be. If you have the experience of playing a high level bard, you simply realize that the epic adds signifigantly to your class. It's not just &quot;another weapon&quot;.  <p><small><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br>Celdor Dreamweaver - Bard (EQ)<br><a href="http://members.home.net/mahkt/"><b>Midnight Fury</b></a><br><br><i>"Let me tell you something pendejo, you pull any of your crazy shit with us, you flash your piece out on the lanes, I'll take it away from you and stick it up your ass and pull the fucking trigger 'till it goes click...Nobody fucks with the Jesus."</i>
