Ok here we go...<br>
<br>
I dont lead these raids with ANY hopes of gaining anything for myself.  I always wanted to win that eyepatch, yes, but as most of you know I bought the damn thing.  So why do I continue to lead the raids???  Well lets see... there are people who have raided Vox with me since the very beginning... there are people who have attended EVERY raid I have done just to show their support... there are people who always give more than they have to just to make everything go smoothly... there are people who always make the "rough raids" worth it in the end... and those people are the reason I lead the raids.  I dont do it to benefit me.  Believe it or not I only started leading again (under a friends character) in hopes of giving some pallys and bards a shot at their epic pieces.  Whats in it for me?  NOTHING other than the reward of knowing that I was the one who made the effort to make it possible since no one else was leading.  Why would I want to lead Naggy?  I wouldnt... the only thing I could win is that Druid Crook and imho its a piece of shit... but I attend the raids to support the other raiders or the raid leader because its fun.  Try it... maybe you'll see there's more to the game than "total uberness and ph4t l3w7z"<br>
<br>
Let me give you an example of how I feel about loot.  I'll use Duec as an example (despite the whole Assassination thing) because he's one of the people I felt strongly about from the beginning.  He attended every one of my raids and did the pulling.  He also was the one person I could depend on to get corpses out of the pits.  He was also the one person who NEVER bitched about losing.  He would give the extra effort to manage corpse runs and even DIE when he didnt have to just to help others and every time an RBB would drop who do you think I would want to win it?  Duec.  I would have given my all to have seen him get that belt before he leveled.  Why?  Because he earned it.  And he is just ONE example of MANY people I would love to see walk away with something.  Look at people like Roark (ranger) who has been there for EVERY raid I have done... he always donates more than is expected and he always sticks through it through thick and thin... these people are the reason I enjoy doing this. (there are way way too many people who I could mention so dont think Im not grateful to the rest of you)<br>
<br>
I know bards and paladins who have been fighting with me from the start... even from back when Kerna was leading who still need their books and scales... I WANT THEM TO GET THEM.  This is one of the reasons I make the level min on the epics... they have earned it.  Not saying that the new pallys and bards who show havent because Im not trying to eliminate everyone Im just trying to make the odds better for the ones I have the highest hopes for. <br>
<br>
Yesterdays raids lasted over 14 hours... and what did I get out of it?  I got the satisfaction of seeing Glazier and Mogdar each get a pally book... and that made the whole night (despite the trials and tribulations) well more than worth it.  Seeing them two win their books meant more to me than any loot item I could have possibly gotten from that dragon.  Seeing my friends/guildees/and a number of people I dont know come out and give their all to make everything possible was the more rewarding than any "uber dragon loot item" I could have asked for.<br>
<br>
Why?  Because I play for fun, and one of my most rewarding parts of this game is helping people.  Seeing others who are giving and unselfish are the reason I play.  And its the whiney ass bastards who are so hung up on their own needs and wants that make me NOT want to give up my time, plat, and exp to help give the unselfish people an opportunity to win something they want or need.<br>
<br>
My level restrictions arent excluding everyone.  They are only there to help the people I know best, the people who have been with me the longest, and the people who are closer to being able to use the items better odds at winning.  There's still other stuff to win.  And there are always people who arent hung up on the loot who will come and support the raid to replace the arogant fucks who cant see past that.  If you feel that its ME holding you back then start bitching at people for not leading the raids at all.  Im not the only god damn person who can lead a successful dragon raid.  So why give me shit when I do and it doesnt meet your requirements?<br>
<br>
Last night I collected donations before Naggy to cover dot costs... at the end of the night I was over 400pp in the hole considering the number of people who dont donate and because I always buy WAY too many dots (just in case).  And its rather amuzing (not pointing fingers and Im not referring to Stan) how the majority of the whiney people who bitch at me about my loot rules (in tells and trust me I get tons of them) are the ones who have never given me a plat towards the cost of the raids.... hmmm... does that make me think my rules are unfair at all?  NO.  Im not bitching about the cost because I could care less... like I said before I do it for fun and having to fork out plat for dots/coffins is just one of the things I choose to do.  And there have been others (clerics who have used their own dots at their own expense or people who have brought their own coffins) who know its just part of the game and are willing to make those sacrifices.  And imho those are the people who I'd like to see walk away with a prize at the end of the night.  <br>
<br>
I've done raids with no restrictions and have seen a lvl 48 who I've never raided with before walk away with an epic item.  And then never see them again.  Does that make me feel rewarded?  Not really.  Does it make me feel as if higher level raiders were cheated out of an opportunity?  Yeah, it does.  Because those higher leveled raiders had put a lot more time and effort into getting their epic pieces (most of them atleast) and most of them are people I respect, and have raided with before, and those are the people that Im rooting for each and every one of them when it comes to winning.  Am I giving them an edge... you bet your ass I am.  Do I deserve to have people piss a fit over it?  No... go fuck yourself if you dont like it honestly because you are the people who are taking the fun out of what I do and frankly Im sick and tired of it.<br>
<br>
Those people who come with no expectations other than the ones having a good time and "POSSIBLY" walking home with an item are the people I will continue to fight for... the people who have to bitch are the reason I wont.  <br>
<br>
And its been said before and I'll say it again... Rather than bitching about my loot rules run your own raids, or go with someone else who leads them... but eat a dick before you decide to send me a tell, or post a rant with your feelings of my loot rules and how they are unfair to you or others... because I dont give a shit what you think.<br>
<br>
